news.title: Gujarat HC tells Ahmedabad civic body to provide shelter to slum dwellers
news.para: On December 22, AMC issued eviction notices to 270 units located between Limda Chowk and Macchi Bazaar in Rakhial, for road widening work stipulated in the town planning scheme.

news.title: FIR against two IAS officers, KDMC staff for illegal building in Kalyan
news.para: The KDMC bosses and town planners are accused of conniving with the developer and allowing the redevelopment of a property in violation of rules starting January 2004.

news.title: NGT panel's report: No sand mining at Cooum river mouth
news.para: No sand mining or transportation activities were observed at Cooum River mouth, according to an inspection report submitted by a National Green Tribunal (NGT) joint-committee.

news.title: Six held, 18 FIRs filed in Bengaluru development body corner sites scam
news.para: According to the officers, the suspects mainly targeted sites in Sir M Visvesvaraya Layout, Arkavathi Layout, HBR Layout and Nadaprabhu Kempegowda Layout and areas in Anjanapura, Banashankari, JP Nagar and Nagarabavi.

news.title: Ludhiana: Unique ID project for properties in limbo
news.para: Officials now claim that due to imposition of election code, the tenders cannot be floated and moreover the officials are yet to get necessary approvals under Smart City mission for the project.

news.title: Indore administration provides possession to four plot buyers in Satellite Hills
news.para: “There are around 90 complainants, who had purchased plots in Satellite Hills but were not provided the possession by the colonizers including Ritesh alias Champu Ajmera and his partners” ADM Abhay Bedekar said.

news.title: Ahmedabad: Properties with over Rs 1 lakh pending tax to be sealed
news.para: “We will be issuing notices to property owners whose pending tax exceeds Rs 1 lakh. If the amount is still not paid, we will seal their premises. On the other hand, we have decided to reward taxpayers who pay up in time,” said Jainik Vakil, chairman of AMC’s revenue committee.

news.title: Lucknow development body to develop a new sector in its Vasantkunj Yojana
news.para: To be named as Sector 'A', LDA has prepared a layout of the project which will include establishments like schools, nursing homes, community centres, parks, housing and commercial units as well.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body demolishes five units without building-use nod
news.para: The residential units from which illegal constructions were demolished were located in TP scheme 36 in Chandlodia while commercial units were located in Nikol.

news.title: Embassy REIT gets right of first offer for Chennai property
news.para: "The acquisition, which comprises nearly 5 million sq ft of office assets in Old Pallavaram, Chennai, is expected to take around six months and is under review," said two people aware of the deal. The property is currently under construction and has 1.4 million sq ft of completed and leased space to clients like BNY Mellon, Accenture and Wells Fargo.

news.title: Kolkata civic body seeks stricter rules for unsafe buildings
news.para: Mayor Firhad Hakim, replying to a query from Ellora Saha, a councillor representing Burrabazar, on acquisition of extremely vulnerable buildings on Friday, said efforts were on to save the lives of residents of the city’s rickety buildings by vacating them and demolishing the dangerous portions.

news.title: Telangana high court closes two pleas of Dalmia Cements
news.para: But in the meantime, they appeared before the ED authorities who issued them summons under section 50 of the Prevention of Money Laundering Act (PMLA). Their statements too were recorded.

news.title: CREDAI Bengaluru urges state government to withdraw night curfew
news.para: The letter stated, “Night curfew has no significance because people coming in close contact at night is minimum. Only lounge bars or big gatherings may have to follow some basic protocol,” the member said.

news.title: Can't refer government dispute with builder to arbitration: Madras HC
news.para: Justice N Anand Venkatesh rejected the plea in view of an archaic arbitration clause added in agreements between the government and private contractors that arbitration will be resorted to only if the value of the dispute was less than ₹50,000.

news.title: Will malls collect fee for using lifts: HC
news.para: Justice PV Kunhikrishnan raised the query while considering a plea by film director Pauly Vadakkan alleging that collection of parking fees at Lulu Mall, Kochi is illegal.
